1
00:00:02,336 --> 00:00:03,268
<i>Previously on</i> Grey's Anatomy...

2
00:00:03,337 --> 00:00:04,777
Aah!

3
00:00:05,089 --> 00:00:06,522
Superman here broke protocol

4
00:00:06,590 --> 00:00:09,069
and ran into the crash to
shield a kid from the blast.

5
00:00:09,093 --> 00:00:10,387
Ethan. Dad.

6
00:00:10,411 --> 00:00:12,105
Stay with Mom, all
right? Where is my mom?

7
00:00:12,129 --> 00:00:14,024
Who are you? It's
me, Mom. Ethan.

8
00:00:14,048 --> 00:00:15,647
No, it's not. Who is he?

9
00:00:15,716 --> 00:00:16,956
No, I'm not going anywhere!

10
00:00:17,017 --> 00:00:18,528
How about we set
you up in a room,

11
00:00:18,552 --> 00:00:20,202
and you can stay with him there?

12
00:00:20,271 --> 00:00:22,303
Brooks, why don't you
step up? Switch with Ross.

13
00:00:22,390 --> 00:00:23,788
God, you have
fast hands, Brooks.

14
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:25,318
<i>I know what you're doing.</i>

15
00:00:25,342 --> 00:00:27,604
Just so we're clear, I'm not
going down without a fight.

16
00:00:27,628 --> 00:00:28,938
I want you to map me.

17
00:00:28,962 --> 00:00:30,842
I want to know if I'm
gonna get Alzheimer's.

18
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:34,344
<i>Patients say it all the time.</i>

19
00:00:34,368 --> 00:00:37,836
<i>"Tell me straight up. I just
want to know what's going on."</i>

20
00:00:37,905 --> 00:00:41,256
Okay, so I've got the results of
your genome sequencing here.

21
00:00:41,325 --> 00:00:43,685
Now we weren't able to get
a clear read off Zola's sample.

22
00:00:43,727 --> 00:00:45,377
Sometimes we just
have to run it again.

23
00:00:45,446 --> 00:00:47,061
But yours came out.

24
00:00:47,131 --> 00:00:48,480
And?

25
00:00:48,549 --> 00:00:49,998
<i>"Tell me. I can handle it."</i>

26
00:00:50,084 --> 00:00:54,119
And, oh, uh, first off, I just
need to ask you a few questions.

27
00:00:54,188 --> 00:00:58,189
We have a couple of different
kinds of, um, information here, so...

28
00:00:58,259 --> 00:00:59,591
I have the gene. Just say it.

29
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:02,761
Look, this test gives
us tons of information.

30
00:01:02,813 --> 00:01:05,180
Some of it's clear.
And some of it isn't.

31
00:01:05,248 --> 00:01:08,116
So, you know, we don't
want to jump to anything

32
00:01:08,185 --> 00:01:09,718
without careful
consideration of...

33
00:01:09,787 --> 00:01:11,264
Yeah, I've carefully considered.

34
00:01:11,288 --> 00:01:13,021
Do I have the Alzheimer's gene?

35
00:01:13,107 --> 00:01:14,751
You gonna let me get
through this questionnaire?

36
00:01:14,775 --> 00:01:16,207
Bailey, you're my mentor

37
00:01:16,277 --> 00:01:18,221
and my friend, and
I respect your work,

38
00:01:18,245 --> 00:01:20,223
but I'm telling you, if you
don't answer my question,

39
00:01:20,247 --> 00:01:21,963
I will punch you in the face.

40
00:01:22,032 --> 00:01:24,800
<i>We don't dodge your
questions 'cause we're mean.</i>

41
00:01:28,255 --> 00:01:30,521
Okay, you have tested positive

42
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:34,359
for more than one of the
genetic markers for Alzheimer's.

43
00:01:34,428 --> 00:01:37,612
<i>We do it because when
you say you want the truth,</i>

44
00:01:37,681 --> 00:01:40,281
<i>you have no idea what
you're talking about.</i>

45
00:01:58,335 --> 00:02:00,535
Shepherd says his wife's
still unconscious, too.

46
00:02:00,604 --> 00:02:02,037
Oh, what did you
do with her kid?

47
00:02:02,106 --> 00:02:05,073
Oh, he was in peds
overnight, just so

48
00:02:05,142 --> 00:02:08,076
social services
didn't haul him off.

49
00:02:08,145 --> 00:02:09,611
His grandmother comes today.

50
00:02:09,679 --> 00:02:11,491
You know what? I thought I
was gonna see you last night.

51
00:02:11,515 --> 00:02:12,692
Oh, I got caught
up with a patient.

52
00:02:12,716 --> 00:02:14,349
Ah, that's too bad.

53
00:02:14,418 --> 00:02:17,002
I put on that T-shirt

54
