00:20:05,554 --> 00:20:07,955
What kind of grown man gets
his mommy to pick him up?

509
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:09,706
They have a good relationship.

510
00:20:09,775 --> 00:20:11,742
He respects women.

511
00:20:11,810 --> 00:20:13,293
He has good values.

512
00:20:13,379 --> 00:20:14,478
I think I'm there.

513
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:16,480
Okay, so if you
don't have a clamp,

514
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:18,032
you can just use your hand

515
00:20:18,100 --> 00:20:20,534
and twist the lung
on the hilar axis.

516
00:20:21,954 --> 00:20:23,854
That's it. I see it. Thank you.

517
00:20:23,923 --> 00:20:25,901
You know what? He
doesn't make fun of me.

518
00:20:25,925 --> 00:20:27,165
He thinks I'm brave.

519
00:20:27,227 --> 00:20:29,009
He likes it when I babble.

520
00:20:29,095 --> 00:20:30,527
He's a unicorn.

521
00:20:30,597 --> 00:20:32,529
He's an amazing guy.

522
00:20:32,599 --> 00:20:35,049
Well, then you should
tell him the truth.

523
00:20:37,370 --> 00:20:39,887
I have this really cool
technique for autotransfusion

524
00:20:39,955 --> 00:20:42,489
that I would love to show
you when you're done here.

525
00:20:42,558 --> 00:20:43,558
Mmm.

526
00:20:45,294 --> 00:20:46,526
Not bad, huh?

527
00:20:46,595 --> 00:20:48,757
Who needs a fancy splint
when you have duct tape?

528
00:20:48,781 --> 00:20:50,931
It holds quite nicely. Mmm-hmm.

529
00:20:54,787 --> 00:20:57,704
Twenty-seven new e-mails about
where my research goes next.

530
00:20:57,790 --> 00:21:00,074
It should sound like
a cash register to you.

531
00:21:00,142 --> 00:21:02,238
Can you go bug Shepherd
for his vote, please?

532
00:21:02,262 --> 00:21:04,695
Oh, I plan to, and
I'm sure I'll get it.

533
00:21:04,764 --> 00:21:07,081
Shepherd knows we
bought this hospital so that

534
00:21:07,149 --> 00:21:09,050
we could all be the
doctors we want to be.

535
00:21:09,118 --> 00:21:11,335
I'm not living my dream.

536
00:21:11,403 --> 00:21:14,088
My dreams are big and bright

537
00:21:14,156 --> 00:21:16,857
and filled with
extremely shiny machines

538
00:21:16,926 --> 00:21:19,843
that grow cartilage
out of thin air.

539
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:25,382
I have that dream all the time.

540
00:21:27,253 --> 00:21:30,337
Since you have limited
blood supply, you do this,

541
00:21:30,405 --> 00:21:32,935
and you're giving your
patient their own blood back.

542
00:21:32,959 --> 00:21:34,103
Do you want to give it a try?

543
00:21:34,127 --> 00:21:35,359
Sure.

544
00:21:35,411 --> 00:21:36,411
Mmm.

545
00:21:37,012 --> 00:21:38,512
So,

546
00:21:38,581 --> 00:21:40,931
are you going to
tell this man the truth

547
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,493
or include his
mother in the lie?

548
00:21:42,517 --> 00:21:45,902
Because I cannot get on that
plane without some closure.

549
00:21:46,772 --> 00:21:49,039
Uh, I am so sorry.

550
00:21:49,108 --> 00:21:52,209
You do not need to bother
with my stupid problems.

551
00:21:52,278 --> 00:21:53,894
You have real problems.

552
00:21:53,963 --> 00:21:56,464
Courtship troubles
are everyone's troubles.

553
00:21:56,532 --> 00:21:59,032
Wooing my wife was very tricky.

554
00:21:59,102 --> 00:22:00,734
Well, how'd you win her over?

555
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:01,820
Ahh.

556
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:06,357
A picnic of spiced lamb

557
00:22:06,426 --> 00:22:08,275
under the cypress trees,

558
00:22:08,361 --> 00:22:10,561
almonds dipped in honey,

559
00:22:10,629 --> 00:22:12,897
the words of my heart.

560
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:19,153
Dr. Kepner,

561
00:22:19,222 --> 00:22:21,739
we went to see <i>Terminator 3.</i>

562
00:22:30,883 --> 00:22:33,584
You were right. Cristina
only wants to be the cool aunt.

563
00:22:33,636 --> 00:22:35,147
I'm sorry. I wish I was wrong.

564
00:22:35,171 --> 00:22:36,620
That's okay. What
about Kathleen?

565
00:22:36,689 --> 00:22:38,066
What about Lizzie?
You two got along.

566
00:22:38,090 --> 00:22:39,301
Oh, I forgot about Lizzie.

567
00:22:39,325 --> 00:22:40,669
You know, I don't
want to leave our kids

568
00:22:40,693 --> 00:22:41,953
with somebody you forgot about.

569
00:22:41,977 --> 00:22:43,310
Well, she's the alternate.

570
00:22:43,378 --> 00:22:45,912
Well, it's a disaster plan.
Most disasters don't happen.

571
00:22:45,982 --> 00:22:47,164
They do to us.

572
00:22:47,934 --> 00:22:49,299
That's true.

573
00:22:49,368 --> 00:22:52,486
We have survived an unusual
number of very bad things.

574
00:22:52,572 --> 00:22:54,438
At this point, it ups our odds.

575
00:22:54,490 --> 00:22:56,134
Just send the papers.

576
00:22:56,158 --> 00:22:59,142
Uh, apparently we have never
filled out a health care directive.

577
00:22:59,212 --> 00:23:00,844
The lawyer wants that, too.

578
00:23:00,913 --> 00:23:03,280
Oh, well, I mean,
you know all of this.

579
00:23:03,332 --> 00:23:04,865
I don't want to be a potato.

580
00:23:04,934 --> 00:23:07,245
No extraordinary measures
taken if it's obviously at the end.

581
00:23:07,269 --> 00:23:08,335
He wants it in writing.

582
00:23:08,404 --> 00:23:10,103
It doesn't matter.

583
00:23:10,172 --> 00:23:11,716
We both know you're gonna
give me a lethal dose of morphine

584
00:23:11,740 --> 00:23:13,652
the second I start to
forget where my keys are.

585
00:23:13,676 --> 00:23:14,819
I'm not kidding.

586
00:23:14,843 --> 00:23:16,655
Before we knew
my mother was sick,

587
00:23:16,679 --> 00:23:18,841
she couldn't remember
anything I'd ever said to her.

588
00:23:18,865 --> 00:23:21,009
And I thought it was because
she didn't give a crap about me.

589
00:23:21,033 --> 00:23:22,677
I don't want to put
my kids through that.

590
00:23:22,701 --> 00:23:24,701
You'll give me a lethal
dose, we'll hold hands,

591
00:23:24,737 --> 00:23:26,114
and I'll fade off
into the night.

592
00:23:26,138 --> 00:23:28,639
We will cross that bridge
when we come to it.

593
00:23:32,745 --> 00:23:34,177
More irrigation.

594
00:23:34,247 --> 00:23:36,630
Looks like I'm gonna
have to open this all up.

595
00:23:37,834 --> 00:23:39,699
You doing okay? I'm fine.

596
00:23:39,786 --> 00:23:41,001
You sure?

597
00:23:41,087 --> 00:23:42,397
Dr. Bailey, don't
get all weird on me

598
00:23:42,421 --> 00:23:43,932
because you think you
shattered my psyche.

599
00:23:43,956 --> 00:23:46,022
I knew what I was asking
when I took that test.

600
00:23:46,092 --> 00:23:47,403
Well, if you ever
need to talk...

601
00:23:47,427 --> 00:23:48,427
Stop it.

602
00:23:49,277 --> 00:23:50,527
All right. Fine.

603
00:23:50,596 --> 00:23:53,080
How about we talk about
the sloppy job you're doing

604
00:23:53,148 --> 00:23:54,448
raising those crappy interns?

605
00:23:54,517 --> 00:23:55,716
There you go.

606
00:23:55,784 --> 00:23:57,762
What, she sneezed
all over my patients,

607
00:23:57,786 --> 00:24:00,187
now I have two
post-op infections?

608
00:24:00,256 --> 00:24:01,722
They have no judgment

609
00:24:01,808 --> 00:24:03,674
or common sense.

610
00:24:03,742 --> 00:24:05,593
Mmm. Sorry to butt in, Bailey.

611
00:24:05,661 --> 00:24:08,262
I saw a patient of yours
from a couple of weeks back.

612
00:24:08,331 --> 00:24:10,380
Post-op infection,
pretty extensive.

613
00:24:10,450 --> 00:24:12,610
He's on IV, antibiotics, but
he's gonna need surgery.

614
00:24:12,652 --> 00:24:14,612
You have time today or
you want me to handle it?

615
00:24:14,654 --> 00:24:17,054
What do you mean, "he"?
He's a she, and I saw her.

616
00:24:17,123 --> 00:24:19,968
I'm dealing with her after I
deal with this post-op infection.

617
00:24:19,992 --> 00:24:21,775
It's not a she.

618
00:24:22,611 --> 00:24:24,144
Seth Lepik.

619
00:24:24,213 --> 00:24:25,891
It's not the same patient.

620
00:24:25,915 --> 00:24:27,748
It's a third one.

621
00:24:39,077 --> 00:24:41,211
Three? Have you spoken to Hunt?

622
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:43,057
No, not yet. I thought
it was just two.

623
00:24:43,081 --> 00:24:44,493
Look, I'll take care
of your third patient.

624
00:24:44,517 --> 00:24:46,316
You need to find Hunt.

625
00:24:48,938 --> 00:24:50,178
Which intern was it?

626
00:24:50,206 --> 00:24:51,404
It's Leah Murphy.

627
00:25:02,618 --> 00:25:04,585
Dr. Darwish, can I
get you something?

628
00:25:05,571 --> 00:25:09,472
Oh, no. I'm just looking.

629
00:25:13,312 --> 00:25:15,178
It's quiet.

630
00:25:15,247 --> 00:25:17,882
We don't have a
lot of quiet anymore.

631
00:25:24,073 --> 00:25:26,290
So there's been a big
rainstorm back east,

632
00:25:26,359 --> 00:25:27,657
and your grandma's flight

633
00:25:27,726 --> 00:25:29,587
isn't gonna be able
to get in until tomorrow,

634
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:32,279
so Carol here
from social services

635
00:25:32,348 --> 00:25:35,482
is going to take you to a
place that you can sleep tonight.

636
00:25:35,551 --> 00:25:38,268
Why can't I stay here
like we did last night?

637
00:25:38,337 --> 00:25:40,582
Well, that's not
going to work out.

638
00:25:40,606 --> 00:25:43,023
I don't want to go with her.
My mom and dad are here.

639
00:25:43,092 --> 00:25:44,457
It's gonna be fine, okay?

640
00:25:44,526 --> 00:25:46,454
They're gonna give
you a great dinner.

641
00:25:46,478 --> 00:25:48,406
And they'll probably give
you ice cream for dessert,

642
00:25:48,430 --> 00:25:50,809
and they're gonna let
you play video games, so...

643
00:25:52,234 --> 00:25:53,867
Hey. Hey, hey, hey. Come on.

644
00:25:53,936 --> 00:25:56,069
It's going to be
fine. I promise.

645
00:26:00,643 --> 00:26:02,309
Okay, is that

646
00:26:03,546 --> 00:26:04,945
better?

647
00:26:05,013 --> 00:26:07,125
Yeah, uh... But, uh, practice
it a bunch more times.

648
00:26:07,149 --> 00:26:10,417
The faster you get in and out,
the better your outcomes will be.

649
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:14,132
Promise me you'll kill
me with a lethal injection

650
00:26:14,156 --> 00:26:15,934
before I start to forget
where my keys are.

651
00:26:15,958 --> 00:26:16,958
Of course.

652
00:26:17,025 --> 00:26:18,141
Early.

653
00:26:18,210 --> 00:26:19,821
Not when I set the house on fire

654
00:26:19,845 --> 00:26:21,373
because I forgot
to shut the stove off

655
00:26:21,397 --> 00:26:22,757
or when I'm sitting
in the rocking chair

656
00:26:22,781 --> 00:26:24,693
in the corner of
the nursing home.

657
00:26:24,717 --> 00:26:26,311
I don't want my kids to go
through what I went through...

658
00:26:26,335 --> 00:26:29,236
Mer, you had me
at "lethal injection."

659
00:26:33,642 --> 00:26:35,091
Wow. Is that my door prize?

660
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:37,022
Okay, so you know I was working

661
00:26:37,046 --> 00:26:38,528
with these two
Syrian guys today?

662
00:26:38,597 --> 00:26:40,363
They barely get any
supplies anymore.

663
00:26:40,432 --> 00:26:42,076
I mean, this is all
they have to work with.

664
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:44,001
But the attendings
all pitched in,

665
00:26:44,069 --> 00:26:45,685
and we figured out a whole bunch

666
00:26:45,754 --> 00:26:47,338
of lifesaving
procedures they can do.

667
00:26:48,357 --> 00:26:49,823
That's great.

668
00:26:51,143 --> 00:26:52,509
Yeah. Um...

669
00:26:53,378 --> 00:26:55,712
My point is,

670
00:26:55,781 --> 00:26:59,716
you think you need everything,

671
00:26:59,785 --> 00:27:01,051
but you don't.

672
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:04,454
We could get by without
a lot of stuff, right?

673
00:27:05,323 --> 00:27:07,557
Sure.

674
00:27:07,626 --> 00:27:10,326
What exactly are we
getting by without?

675
00:27:13,431 --> 00:27:14,765
Uh...

676
00:27:16,985 --> 00:27:18,485
My virginity.

677
00:27:20,806 --> 00:27:23,340
I was...

678
00:27:23,409 --> 00:27:26,443
I was a virgin for
a really long time,

679
00:27:26,512 --> 00:27:28,044
and then I wasn't.

680
00:27:30,315 --> 00:27:32,616
I really wanted to wait

681
00:27:33,485 --> 00:27:35,819
for someone like you,

682
00:27:35,888 --> 00:27:37,721
for marriage, but I screwed up.

683
00:27:37,790 --> 00:27:41,158
And I was just... I was
so scared to tell you.

684
00:27:41,226 --> 00:27:43,226
But then I was watching
these guys today,

685
00:27:43,295 --> 00:27:45,262
and they... They
literally have nothing left,

686
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:46,797
and they're making do.

687
00:27:46,866 --> 00:27:49,232
And then I just felt like
I was being so stupid

688
00:27:49,301 --> 00:27:52,335
to worry about
this one little thing,

689
00:27:52,404 --> 00:27:54,972
like you couldn't
even get over it.

690
00:27:56,542 --> 00:27:58,742
So,

691
00:27:58,811 --> 00:28:00,789
I guess I would be
an ungrateful jerk

692
00:28:00,813 --> 00:28:02,624
if I worried about
your virginity

693
00:28:02,648 --> 00:28:05,744
while there's a war going on
somewhere and people are dying?

694
00:28:05,768 --> 00:28:08,128
That what you're saying to me?

695
00:28:09,004 --> 00:28:10,937
No, no. I didn't...

696
00:28:11,006 --> 00:28:13,366
You didn't think I'd be
more hung up on the lying?

697
00:28:15,043 --> 00:28:18,511
'Cause I bet even in a war,
people still value honesty.

698
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:29,839
He's still not awake?

699
00:28:29,908 --> 00:28:31,148
Uh, no, not yet.

700
00:28:31,209 --> 00:28:33,355
I gave him a bolus of
D50. We'll see if that helps.

701
00:28:33,379 --> 00:28:35,562
Why didn't you talk to me first?

702
00:28:35,631 --> 00:28:38,426
Because I talked to Russell
about it, like you asked me to.

703
00:28:38,450 --> 00:28:40,461
But you knew that I was
concerned about this case.

704
00:28:40,485 --> 00:28:43,069
You really want me to have
three highly trained surgeons

705
00:28:43,138 --> 00:28:44,832
supervising one man's recovery?

706
00:28:44,856 --> 00:28:47,740
It shouldn't be news to you that
we work as a team at this hospital.

707
00:28:47,809 --> 00:28:51,094
Yes, and the entire team is
helping you save Syria from itself.

708
00:28:51,147 --> 00:28:54,326
I came up with, like, 14 ways
of doing thoracotomy procedures

709
00:28:54,350 --> 00:28:55,715
without a chest tray.

710
00:28:55,784 --> 00:28:57,295
I didn't have time
for a groupthink

711
00:28:57,319 --> 00:28:59,386
on perfectly
straightforward post-op care.

712
00:28:59,454 --> 00:29:00,598
Tomorrow, you, Russell, myself

713
00:29:00,622 --> 00:29:01,933
will round on Paul
together, all right?

714
00:29:01,957 --> 00:29:03,223
Are you serious? I am.

715
00:29:03,292 --> 00:29:05,203
Uh, Dr. Hunt, I need
to speak with you.

716
00:29:05,227 --> 00:29:06,309
Could you give me moment?

717
00:29:06,378 --> 00:29:08,345
It has to be now.

718
00:29:08,414 --> 00:29:10,847
And Webber's in
the OR with the third.

719
00:29:10,916 --> 00:29:14,184
So we have no idea
how extensive this is?

720
00:29:15,671 --> 00:29:17,120
All right.

721
00:29:17,188 --> 00:29:18,533
You and I are gonna need
to talk to infection control,

722
00:29:18,557 --> 00:29:19,868
let them know
what we know so far.

723
00:29:19,892 --> 00:29:21,870
I need you to find all
your charts from that day,

724
00:29:21,894 --> 00:29:24,288
figure out every patient
you touched in post-op,

725
00:29:24,312 --> 00:29:25,679
or anywhere, for that matter.

726
00:29:25,748 --> 00:29:27,158
We're gonna need to
call every one of them,

727
00:29:27,182 --> 00:29:28,960
have them come in,
and examine them.

728
00:29:28,984 --> 00:29:31,265
This is going to be a nightmare.

729
00:29:35,173 --> 00:29:36,651
They're gonna
fire me, aren't they?

730
00:29:36,675 --> 00:29:38,075
Just go.

731
00:29:48,370 --> 00:29:50,103
Still unconscious?

732
00:29:53,675 --> 00:29:55,358
Bummer.

733
00:29:55,427 --> 00:29:57,038
It's okay. He'll wake
up in a couple of days,

734
00:29:57,062 --> 00:29:59,229
if we can all relax
and be patient about it.

735
00:29:59,298 --> 00:30:01,314
Good. Yeah, tell that to Owen.

736
00:30:01,383 --> 00:30:03,917
We may be losing Leah
Murphy from the program.

737
00:30:04,003 --> 00:30:05,485
Did I like her?

738
00:30:05,554 --> 00:30:07,921
I think you said once
that she didn't suck

739
00:30:07,989 --> 00:30:09,822
as much as you
expected her to suck.

740
00:30:09,892 --> 00:30:11,524
Oh. That's too bad.

741
00:30:11,593 --> 00:30:13,943
You know, maybe Owen
doesn't like being Chief.

742
00:30:14,013 --> 00:30:15,178
What makes you say that?

743
00:30:15,231 --> 00:30:16,496
I thought he did,

744
00:30:16,565 --> 00:30:18,276
but lately, he's had
a bug up his butt

745
00:30:18,300 --> 00:30:20,212
about Russell not
supervising me.

746
00:30:20,236 --> 00:30:22,536
You know, maybe it's
because he misses teaching.

747
00:30:22,605 --> 00:30:25,083
I mean, Derek, he hated
all that administrative crap

748
00:30:25,107 --> 00:30:26,517
when he was Chief,
right? Mmm-hmm.

749
00:30:26,541 --> 00:30:28,470
Owen's had nothing
but that for weeks.

750
00:30:28,494 --> 00:30:31,056
Maybe he feels like he's
losing touch with the medicine?

751
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:35,365
Or maybe it's because
Russell's not supervising you.

752
00:30:35,433 --> 00:30:39,064
Okay, I just agreed to off you
the minute you started acting dotty.

753
00:30:39,088 --> 00:30:40,816
Shouldn't you be on my
side for the rest of the day

754
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:42,572
just as a courtesy?

755
00:30:44,376 --> 00:30:46,421
Ross was working
the pit today? Yes.

756
00:30:46,445 --> 00:30:48,945
Okay, I just took out
an infected dialysis graft.

757
00:30:49,014 --> 00:30:50,659
Mmm-hmm. He saw
the patient before I did...

758
00:30:50,683 --> 00:30:52,427
Right. but he didn't
scrub in with me

759
00:30:52,451 --> 00:30:55,163
because he wanted to make sure
your MRI was just the way you liked it.

760
00:30:55,187 --> 00:30:56,947
Hey, Dr. Webber.

761
00:30:56,972 --> 00:30:58,583
Someone just put a
glioblastoma resection

762
00:30:58,607 --> 00:30:59,906
on your schedule for tomorrow.

763
00:30:59,975 --> 00:31:02,959
Did you want to do that
before or after your aneurysm?

764
00:31:05,764 --> 00:31:07,830
Shane, you have to stop.

765
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:09,499
I am working with Brooks now.

766
00:31:09,567 --> 00:31:12,485
Yeah, but she annoys
you, doesn't she?

767
00:31:12,554 --> 00:31:14,883
Mmm. I mean, you
and I kind of get along.

768
00:31:14,907 --> 00:31:17,269
Brooks has an instinct
for this that you don't have.

769
00:31:17,293 --> 00:31:19,271
You make up for it
with a ton of work.

770
00:31:19,295 --> 00:31:21,811
Well, if I'm making up
for it, who cares how?

771
00:31:23,048 --> 00:31:24,314
I care.

772
00:31:24,383 --> 00:31:25,682
And you should, too.

773
00:31:25,751 --> 00:31:28,735
You should find a
specialty where you shine.

774
00:31:28,804 --> 00:31:30,837
This is what I'm
passionate about.

775
00:31:30,906 --> 00:31:32,689
Doesn't that count for anything?

776
00:31:32,758 --> 00:31:34,903
She's better at
this than you are.

777
00:31:34,927 --> 00:31:37,995
And that means, to me, I
have to teach her, not you.

778
00:31:38,063 --> 00:31:39,540
You're gonna be a great surgeon.

779
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:41,298
Go figure out where.

780
00:31:41,367 --> 00:31:42,832
Hey.

781
00:31:52,777 --> 00:31:54,777
Guy can't take a hint, huh?

782
00:31:55,497 --> 00:31:57,214
Mmm-hmm.

783
00:31:57,282 --> 00:31:58,915
Where are we going, sensei?

784
00:31:58,984 --> 00:32:02,519
We are going to check
in on Rachel Dawson,

785
00:32:02,588 --> 00:32:04,349
see if her neuro
exams have improved.

786
00:32:04,373 --> 00:32:05,767
You went with
spearmint gum this time.

787
00:32:05,791 --> 00:32:07,357
Yeah. You can smell it?

788
00:32:07,426 --> 00:32:08,546
Mmm. I can.

789
00:32:08,577 --> 00:32:09,676
Do you like spearmint?

790
00:32:09,745 --> 00:32:11,177
Not really, no.

791
00:32:11,246 --> 00:32:12,929
Just use peripheral
vascular instruments

792
00:32:12,998 --> 00:32:14,675
if you don't have
stuff for peds. Mmm.

793
00:32:14,699 --> 00:32:17,267
Okay, so pass the umbilical
tape around the vessel.

794
00:32:17,335 --> 00:32:19,402
And then thread both ends

795
00:32:19,471 --> 00:32:21,471
through the short
rubber catheter

796
00:32:21,506 --> 00:32:23,039
and place the hemostat.

797
00:32:23,108 --> 00:32:25,258
There.

798
00:32:25,327 --> 00:32:26,955
Uh, could I borrow
her for a moment?

799
00:32:26,979 --> 00:32:28,711
Yes, but not for long, please.

800
00:32:32,217 --> 00:32:34,796
Uh, I would like to admit Ethan
Dawson to peds for the night.

801
00:32:34,820 --> 00:32:37,215
Oh, he'll be fine with social
services. Kids go with them every day.

802
00:32:37,239 --> 00:32:38,466
This kid doesn't have to.

803
00:32:38,490 --> 00:32:40,206
Owen, there's
protocol for a reason.

804
00:32:40,292 --> 00:32:42,103
Yeah, but we're
human for a reason.

805
00:32:42,127 --> 00:32:44,544
I know that you've taken a
special interest in this kid...

806
00:32:44,613 --> 00:32:46,891
Why is everybody acting like this
is some kind of a character flaw?

807
00:32:46,915 --> 00:32:48,081
He ought to stay. He's sick.

808
00:32:48,150 --> 00:32:50,083
I got a look at him
when I checked his wrist.

809
00:32:50,151 --> 00:32:51,517
Short limb syndrome.

810
00:32:51,587 --> 00:32:52,835
Karev.

811
00:32:52,888 --> 00:32:54,488
Right. He's right.

812
00:32:54,556 --> 00:32:57,824
Uh, limited growth,
excessive sleeping, and eating.

813
00:32:57,893 --> 00:32:59,242
Impulse control problems.

814
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:01,244
These are all the
symptoms of childhood.

815
00:33:01,313 --> 00:33:02,745
Can't be sure.

816
00:33:02,815 --> 00:33:05,448
Not until we confirm it
with testing and observation.

817
00:33:05,517 --> 00:33:08,018
Guys, guys, I love
the enthusiasm,

818
00:33:08,086 --> 00:33:09,919
but it's not gonna happen.

819
00:33:10,823 --> 00:33:12,739
All right.

820
00:33:18,714 --> 00:33:20,247
Hey.

821
00:33:20,315 --> 00:33:23,182
Cristina said she would pull
the trigger if it comes to that.

822
00:33:24,853 --> 00:33:26,119
You're my wife.

823
00:33:26,187 --> 00:33:27,665
Can we make the
decision together

824
00:33:27,689 --> 00:33:29,809
if we're gonna
throw in the towel?

825
00:33:30,075 --> 00:33:31,408
That sounds fair.

826
00:33:31,477 --> 00:33:33,597
It's not gonna be easy
on you if I start to lose it.

827
00:33:33,629 --> 00:33:34,911
Oh, don't worry.

828
00:33:34,963 --> 00:33:37,063
You're a project even
with all your marbles.

829
00:33:38,299 --> 00:33:39,911
I brought you
something. You did?

830
00:33:39,935 --> 00:33:41,613
I had Bailey do my genome.

831
00:33:41,637 --> 00:33:43,670
You did? Yeah.

832
00:33:43,739 --> 00:33:46,956
High-risk for liver cancer
and prostate cancer? Whoa.

833
00:33:47,026 --> 00:33:49,308
Yeah. You're telling me.

834
00:33:49,395 --> 00:33:50,827
Male pattern baldness?

835
00:33:51,897 --> 00:33:53,597
Late onset, apparently.

836
00:33:53,665 --> 00:33:54,698
Mmm-hmm.

837
00:33:54,767 --> 00:33:56,082
Heroin addiction?

838
00:33:56,151 --> 00:33:57,294
I'm a real prize. Oh.

839
00:33:57,318 --> 00:33:58,718
It's all a crapshoot.

840
00:33:58,787 --> 00:34:00,331
We didn't get
one single definite.

841
00:34:00,355 --> 00:34:01,471
We only got maybes.

842
00:34:01,540 --> 00:34:02,972
Ah, maybe we live forever.

843
00:34:03,042 --> 00:34:05,958
Maybe we do, and maybe I
become a bald heroin addict.

844
00:34:26,181 --> 00:34:28,798
Honey, I'm gonna take
these bags down to the car.

845
00:34:28,867 --> 00:34:30,867
Thanks, Mom.

846
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:43,246
Wrapping it up for the day?

847
00:34:43,315 --> 00:34:45,214
Yep.

848
00:34:45,284 --> 00:34:46,949
How about you let
me buy you dinner?

849
00:34:47,002 --> 00:34:49,230
I want to bend your ear about
a project I'm thinking about.

850
00:34:49,254 --> 00:34:50,787
You and everyone else

851
00:34:50,856 --> 00:34:53,106
are free to submit
your proposals in writing

852
00:34:53,175 --> 00:34:54,574
to the entire board.

853
00:34:54,643 --> 00:34:56,154
And then I will vote
like everyone else does.

854
00:34:56,178 --> 00:34:57,455
Hell, maybe I'll
submit one myself.

855
00:34:57,479 --> 00:34:58,861
Maybe I have an idea,

856
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:00,841
but I'm not out here
hawking it to people at work.

857
00:35:00,865 --> 00:35:02,610
'Cause I'm gonna
write a proposal

858
00:35:02,634 --> 00:35:04,033
like you're supposed to.

859
00:35:06,287 --> 00:35:08,121
Um... Son,

860
00:35:09,390 --> 00:35:11,908
nobody's ever saying
yes to your proposal.

861
00:35:11,976 --> 00:35:13,910
You're the most powerful
vote on the board.

862
00:35:13,979 --> 00:35:16,124
You're the person who says
yes to other people's ideas.

863
00:35:16,148 --> 00:35:17,947
We still let you be a surgeon.

864
00:35:18,016 --> 00:35:19,833
Nobody wanted to
take that away from you.

865
00:35:19,902 --> 00:35:22,652
But your project
is this hospital.

866
00:35:24,089 --> 00:35:26,523
Yeah, it's exhausting sometimes.

867
00:35:27,275 --> 00:35:28,507
Yeah.

868
00:35:31,213 --> 00:35:34,080
You know something I
learned when I was the Chief?

869
00:35:34,149 --> 00:35:36,049
What?

870
00:35:36,118 --> 00:35:38,167
Somebody offers
to buy you dinner

871
00:35:38,236 --> 00:35:40,102
while they talk
your ear off about

872
00:35:40,171 --> 00:35:41,988
something you
don't want to hear...

873
00:35:44,543 --> 00:35:46,342
You say yes.

874
00:35:46,395 --> 00:35:50,129
Look at that. You're a natural.

875
00:35:52,100 --> 00:35:53,294
Oh, looks like you got this.

876
00:35:53,318 --> 00:35:54,667
Yes,

877
00:35:54,736 --> 00:35:56,769
but not as fast as it could be.

878
00:35:57,805 --> 00:36:00,023
Practice, practice, practice.

879
00:36:02,510 --> 00:36:04,593
Thank you for all
you've taught us.

880
00:36:06,131 --> 00:36:08,881
I wish it could be more.
It feels like nothing.

881
00:36:08,951 --> 00:36:11,551
If we will help even one child,

882
00:36:11,619 --> 00:36:12,885
it's everything.

883
00:36:15,057 --> 00:36:16,906
Short limb syndrome?

884
00:36:16,975 --> 00:36:18,853
Mmm-hmm. Yeah, we're not sure.

885
00:36:18,877 --> 00:36:20,188
At this point, we're just
admitting him for observation.

886
00:36:20,212 --> 00:36:21,689
We'll know more in the morning.

887
00:36:21,713 --> 00:36:23,779
Thank you.

888
00:36:23,849 --> 00:36:25,949
Hey. So got your own TV,

889
00:36:26,017 --> 00:36:28,363
they serve a chocolate
pudding that's not half bad,

890
00:36:28,387 --> 00:36:31,987
and I'm gonna see if I can scare
up some comic books, okay?

891
00:36:33,709 --> 00:36:34,908
Hey.

892
00:36:34,977 --> 00:36:36,208
You okay?

893
00:36:36,278 --> 00:36:38,327
You just told the
nurse I was sick.

894
00:36:38,397 --> 00:36:40,563
Yeah, you're fake sick.

895
00:36:40,616 --> 00:36:42,315
The nurse knows that. Even...

896
00:36:42,401 --> 00:36:43,800
All the doctors know it.

897
00:36:43,869 --> 00:36:45,847
We're just pretending so
you can stay here tonight.

898
00:36:45,871 --> 00:36:48,071
There is nothing wrong with you.

899
00:36:49,758 --> 00:36:51,608
Is it fake with my mom and dad?

900
00:36:54,595 --> 00:36:55,762
No.

901
00:36:56,865 --> 00:36:58,498
No, I wish it was.

902
00:36:59,350 --> 00:37:00,951
My dad's still not awake?

903
00:37:02,487 --> 00:37:03,836
No, he's not.

904
00:37:03,922 --> 00:37:05,888
Is he ever gonna wake up?

905
00:37:11,713 --> 00:37:13,396
I don't know.

906
00:37:19,103 --> 00:37:21,170
So, you played soccer.

907
00:37:21,239 --> 00:37:22,972
I did.

908
00:37:23,041 --> 00:37:25,691
Hey. Owen's been acting crazy.

909
00:37:25,777 --> 00:37:27,360
I think this is why.

910
00:37:27,428 --> 00:37:29,879
The left defender is crucial.

911
00:37:29,948 --> 00:37:31,747
Kids make you crazy.

912
00:37:33,084 --> 00:37:34,384
Yeah.

913
00:37:35,686 --> 00:37:37,020
Kind of cute, though.

914
00:37:37,089 --> 00:37:38,454
Dr. Grey.

915
00:37:43,428 --> 00:37:44,794
I'm not gonna get fired.

916
00:37:44,862 --> 00:37:47,413
We'll cross that bridge
when we come to it.

917
00:37:47,482 --> 00:37:49,516
No, it's worse than that.

918
00:37:57,208 --> 00:37:59,576
Dr. Bailey, Joyce is crashing.

919
00:38:00,846 --> 00:38:02,228
What?

920
00:38:19,748 --> 00:38:23,349
Dr. Kepner, you have given
us piles of supplies already.

921
00:38:23,418 --> 00:38:25,618
This equipment is expensive.

922
00:38:25,686 --> 00:38:28,955
Yeah. Yeah, but
this will really help.

923
00:38:29,024 --> 00:38:32,391
Oh, and you should
definitely take this.

924
00:38:32,477 --> 00:38:34,727
It's an infrascanner.

925
00:38:34,796 --> 00:38:36,629
It can detect a brain bleed.

926
00:38:36,697 --> 00:38:38,264
Oh. Oh.

927
00:38:40,435 --> 00:38:41,768
Uh...

928
00:38:41,836 --> 00:38:44,036
Are you sure this is all right?

929
00:38:44,106 --> 00:38:46,405
Perhaps you need
to talk to Dr. Hunt.

930
00:38:47,658 --> 00:38:49,541
Don't worry about it.

931
00:38:51,779 --> 00:38:54,063
Honesty's not all
it's cracked up to be.

932
00:39:00,738 --> 00:39:03,756
<i>They say the truth
will set you free.</i>

933
00:39:10,465 --> 00:39:13,299
<i>What the hell do they know?</i>

934
00:39:25,897 --> 00:39:28,965
<i>The truth is
horrible, frightening.</i>

935
00:39:48,019 --> 00:39:50,837
<i>The truth is more
than you can bear.</i>

936
00:39:53,475 --> 00:39:56,153
Bailey said the second patient
isn't responding to antibiotics.

937
00:39:56,177 --> 00:39:58,077
So she's going to need surgery.

938
00:39:58,146 --> 00:40:01,246
I just operated on the third.

939
00:40:01,316 --> 00:40:03,249
He's hypotensive and
still pretty unstable.

940
00:40:03,318 --> 00:40:05,963
Once Murphy's identified
all her patients for the day,

941
00:40:05,987 --> 00:40:09,038
then we'll get them in here,
make sure no one else is infected.

942
00:40:09,107 --> 00:40:10,885
We're gonna need to make
some kind of statement.

943
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:12,789
Before this gets
out there on its own.

944
00:40:13,745 --> 00:40:14,944
Hey, uh,

945
00:40:15,012 --> 00:40:17,280
the first patient, Joyce Basche,

946
00:40:17,349 --> 00:40:19,282
she didn't make it.

947
00:40:19,351 --> 00:40:21,479
I thought that the surgery
would get rid of the infection,

948
00:40:21,503 --> 00:40:23,035
but...

949
00:40:23,104 --> 00:40:25,738
You need to get cultures
on the other two right away.

950
00:40:25,807 --> 00:40:27,985
And we need to make sure that
we're using the right antibiotics

951
00:40:28,009 --> 00:40:29,336
so that this doesn't
get out of control.

952
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:30,526
Okay.

953
00:40:31,696 --> 00:40:33,696
We just lost Joyce Basche.

954
00:40:33,765 --> 00:40:35,064
Dr. Bailey...

955
00:40:35,133 --> 00:40:36,543
No, she's her patient.
She should know.

956
00:40:36,567 --> 00:40:37,995
Leah checked all the charts.

957
00:40:38,019 --> 00:40:40,113
She was only on two of the
patients that got the infection.

958
00:40:40,137 --> 00:40:41,866
She never touched the third one.

959
00:40:41,890 --> 00:40:44,990
What, is that supposed to
reassure me? A woman just died.

960
00:40:45,060 --> 00:40:47,610
It couldn't have been Leah.

961
00:40:47,679 --> 00:40:50,680
The only doctor who
touched all three patients

962
00:40:50,732 --> 00:40:51,864
was you.

963
00:40:56,071 --> 00:40:58,637
We're gonna need
to get legal down here.

964
00:40:58,707 --> 00:41:01,803
Wait. Anything could've
caused this kind of infection.

965
00:41:01,827 --> 00:41:03,726
Yeah, no...

966
00:41:03,795 --> 00:41:06,245
Well, we know that, but
until there's an investigation...

967
00:41:06,331 --> 00:41:08,443
No, I gotta go, 'cause I
have two more people...

968
00:41:08,467 --> 00:41:09,649
Owen?

969
00:41:09,717 --> 00:41:10,862
Dr. Webber will deal with them.

970
00:41:10,886 --> 00:41:12,029
Yeah, this is Dr. Avery.

971
00:41:12,053 --> 00:41:13,330
Get me Joelle Geller from legal

972
00:41:13,354 --> 00:41:15,194
down here, conference room two.

973
00:41:15,923 --> 00:41:17,223
I will

974
00:41:17,309 --> 00:41:18,824
go over my notes.

975
00:41:18,894 --> 00:41:20,877
Sit down, Dr. Bailey.

976
00:41:21,862 --> 00:41:24,897
No. My patients are in danger.

977
00:41:24,966 --> 00:41:27,086
Dr. Webber will
take care of them.

978
00:41:28,036 --> 00:41:29,680
I haven't even told

979
00:41:29,704 --> 00:41:31,432
Joyce's husband
that she didn't make it.

980
00:41:35,777 --> 00:41:37,342
I know the man!

981
00:41:37,412 --> 00:41:40,512
I don't need Grey to tell
him that I killed his wife!

982
00:41:40,582 --> 00:41:42,714
Dr. Bailey, please sit down.

983
00:41:47,739 --> 00:41:50,017
<i>We're supposed to
be straight with you,</i>

984
00:41:50,041 --> 00:41:53,709
<i>so be careful what you ask for
when you walk into a hospital.</i>

985
00:41:53,778 --> 00:41:55,861
What are you saying?

986
00:41:55,931 --> 00:41:58,231
I'm asking you to sit down.

987
00:42:12,447 --> 00:42:15,782
<i>Because when you find
out what's really going on,</i>

988
00:42:16,851 --> 00:42:18,584
<i>you may never recover.</i>
